	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lens&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Concave&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;Binoculars, Telescopes, cameras, the lens for a person suffering from myopia, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Plano concave&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;They are used to expand light beams or to increase focal lengths on optical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Cylindrical&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;ul&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;It is typically used to focus, condense, or expand an incoming light.&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;li&gt;It can also be used to expand the output of a laser diode into a symmetrical beam.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
